The second volume of "Xi Jinping: The Governance of China" has been published in five ethnic minority languages.The translation and publication of the ethnic minority language versions -- Mongolian, Tibetan, Uygur, Kazak, and Korean -- are aimed at helping people learn about and apply Xi Jinping Thought on Socialism with Chinese Characteristics for a New Era, according to a statement provided to Xinhua Thursday.Divided into 17 sections by topic, the second volume contains a compilation of 99 of Xi's spoken and written works from Aug. 18, 2014 to Sept. 29, 2017, along with 29 related photographs.It depicts the great practice of the Communist Party of China Central Committee with Comrade Xi Jinping at its core in uniting and leading the whole Party and the Chinese people of all ethnic groups to uphold and develop socialism with Chinese characteristics in a new era.It also chronicles the development and outlines the main content of the Xi Jinping Thought on Socialism with Chinese Characteristics for a New Era. Chinese scientists design gene-editing tool using light to kill cancer cellsAbsence at PLA maritime parade will prevent US from learning about Chinese Navy: expertsChinese American organization condemns increasing racial profiling in US Utah celebrates 150th birthday of Transcontinental RailroadActress Liu honored with Hollywood Walk of Fame star